# swim-ui Demo: Match ngx-ui Demo Usage

When creating or updating the **swim-ui demo** (e.g. `projects/swimlane/swim-ui/demo/index.html` and `demo/src/main.ts`), use the **ngx-ui demo app** under the repo root **`src/app`** as the reference so usage and structure stay aligned.

## Where ngx-ui demos live

- **Controls (input + select + button together):** `src/app/controls-page/`
  - Alignment table (no labels / with labels / with hints / multiline hints)
  - Flexbox and stacked layout examples
  - Responsive validation
- **Buttons:** `src/app/forms/buttons-page/`
  - ngx-button (variants, promise/state, disabled), native buttons, links, with icons, sizes, states table, file upload, long-press
  - Each block in `<ngx-section sectionTitle="...">` with `<app-prism>` code after
- **Inputs:** `src/app/forms/inputs-page/`
  - Text, prefix/suffix, disabled, readonly, unlockable, with hint; then types (number, textarea, etc.)
  - Sections: "Text", "Number", "Textarea", etc., with example + prism per subsection
- **Selects:** `src/app/forms/selects-page/`
  - Single select: Basic, Required, Filtering, Filtering (numerics), Case sensitive, Add New, etc.
  - Uses options like "Attack Type" (Breach, DDOS, Physical) for consistency
  - Multi-select, tagging, appearances, sizes, states
- **Tabs:** `src/app/components/tabs-page/`
  - Examples tab: "Basic Tabs", "Tab Controls" (prev/next/select), "ngFor Tabs", "Custom Label Tabs", "Variants" (vertical, appearance light)
  - Each section has live example then `<app-prism>` with markup

## Structure to mirror

1. **Page/section layout**
   - Use a clear component title (e.g. "Button", "Input", "Select", "Tabs") then logical sections.
   - Each section: short heading (e.g. "Basic", "With Filtering", "Vertical Tabs") → live example(s) → code sample (e.g. `<pre><code>...</code></pre>` or prism-style block).
   - **Collapsible panels**: Where ngx-ui uses `<ngx-section sectionTitle="...">` around a block, use **`<swim-section section-title="...">`** in the Lit demo so each subsection is a collapsible panel matching the Angular component demo. Wrap the content inside each `<section class="section">` with `<swim-section section-title="...">` (same title as the section heading). Omit or set `section-collapsible="false"` only when the Angular demo does.

2. **Example content**
   - Where the same use case exists in ngx-ui, mirror it in swim-ui (e.g. same labels, same options, same variants).
   - **Include all color/style variants** for each component: every option the component supports (e.g. Button Group: default and primary; Button: default, primary, warning, danger, bordered, link).
   - Example: for Select, include a "Single Select" example with options like "Attack Type" / Breach, DDOS, Physical to match ngx-ui.
   - Button: Default, Primary, Warning, Danger, Bordered, Link; sizes; states (active, in-progress, success, fail, disabled).
   - Button Group: All color variants (default, primary) in a dedicated "Color variants" or equivalent section; show horizontal and vertical where applicable.
   - Input: Text with label/hint, Disabled, Readonly, prefix/suffix when supported.
   - Tabs: Basic tabs, Vertical, Light appearance, Disabled tab.

3. **Code samples**
   - Show the **Lit/HTML** equivalent of the ngx-ui snippet (e.g. `<swim-button>`, `<swim-input>`, `<swim-select>`, `<swim-tabs>` / `<swim-tab>` with the same attributes and structure as in the demo).

4. **API / docs**
   - ngx-ui pages often have an "API" tab with inputs/outputs tables. For swim-ui, either add a similar "Usage" or "API" section with props/attributes and events that match the component’s public API.

